title: Paul Cezanne Boxed Note Cards
description:
Cards developed from Paul Cezanne’s:  The Plate of Apples, About 1877, The Basket of Apples, About 1893, The Bathers, 1899-1904, Auvers, Panoramic View, 1873-75, and The Bay of Marseille, Seen from L’Estaque, About 1885, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

The cards are made from a sustainable FSC certified mix paper and vegetable-based inks.

  • Card dimensions: 5 x 7 in.
  • Box dimensions: 5.625 x 7.625 x 1.375 in.
  • 20 cards and envelopes, 4 cards each of 5 images.
